<section class="block-section do">
  <span class="section-tag">Do</span>
  <h2>Today's work — choose one path</h2>
  <p class="sub">All four paths advance your Stakeholders Map. The path you pick is about how much you stretch beyond the default first draft.</p>
  <div class="choice-intro">
    <strong>Learning Intention:</strong> I have first-drafted my chosen stakeholder's full 7-field map row and named at least 3 additional stakeholders in my case.
  </div>
  <div class="choice-board">
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">A</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Start your Stakeholders Map (default)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Open your <a href="/units/unit-5/assessment-water-stakeholders/">Stakeholders Map template</a>. Fill your chosen stakeholder's full row — all 7 fields. Then name ≥3 additional stakeholders for your case, with at least 2 fields each (Who They Are + Position is enough for the additional three; full rows come later). Specificity is the K/U gate — "a Karnataka upstream farmer in Mandya district" beats "farmers."</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Default</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">B</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Hydrologist consultation on case hydrology (stretch)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Same as Path A, but use the <a href="/ai-partners/the-hydrologist/">Hydrologist</a> to deepen the "Evidence They Cite" field for your chosen stakeholder. What specific hydrology numbers (allocation volumes, residence times, recharge rates, basin-wide deficit data) would they actually point to? Document the exchange — this is your <a href="/foundations/ai-documentation-protocol/">AI Doc</a> entry for the block, and the K/U-gate verification matters here.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Stretch</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">C</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Source Evaluator OPVL on your strongest source (choice)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">Open the <a href="/ai-partners/the-source-evaluator/">Source Evaluator</a>. OPVL the single source you currently consider strongest on your case. Specificity in the Limitation is what makes it count. The OPVL feeds the Background section of your Position Paper.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Solo · Choice</span>
    </div>
    <div class="choice">
      <div class="choice-letter">D</div>
      <div class="choice-title">Peer-help — what counts as a "specific" stakeholder (practice)</div>
      <div class="choice-detail">The K/U gate is <em>specific</em>, not <em>generic</em>. "Tamil Nadu" isn't a stakeholder — the Tamil Nadu state government is, and so are Tamil Nadu delta rice farmers, and Tamil Nadu drinking-water consumers, and Tamil Nadu fishing communities at the river mouth — and they often disagree with each other. If specificity is fuzzy, come to the peer-help table. Mr. Ignash + a peer will help you sharpen your stakeholder definition.</div>
      <span class="udl-tag">Pairs · Practice</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

